Hi S. Sharma,

As part of an internal effort to clean up how Technijian time entries appear =
on client invoices, I ran a review of every time entry logged across all clie=
nts during 2026. The goal is not to audit anyone =E2=80=94 it is to give each=
 tech a personal view of where the entries they log might look unreasonable t=
o a client reading their weekly in-contract invoice, so we can correct things=
 before the invoice is committed.

Your 2026 numbers:
  - You logged 401 time entries totalling 276.28 hours across all clients.
  - The audit flagged 5 entries (6.57 hours) =E2=80=94 1.2% by count, 2.4% by=
 hours.

Your most common flag is H1 =E2=80=94 logging more time than expected on rout=
ine work (patch, agent updates, monitoring alerts). The attached training doc=
ument walks through your specific entries and what to change going forward.

Two attachments to review:
  - S-Sharma-Training.docx =E2=80=94 your personalized branded training docum=
ent. Cover page, your stats, breakdown by client and category, your 12 most-f=
lagged entries, and concrete advice on what to write differently next time.
  - flagged-entries.csv =E2=80=94 every flagged entry of yours (client, date,=
 title, hours, cap, flag codes, reasons).

NEW WEEKLY CADENCE =E2=80=94 STARTING THIS WEEK:
Every Thursday we will run this scan against the week's logged entries and em=
ail each tech their personalized flagged-entries list BEFORE Friday's weekly =
in-contract invoice is committed. That gives you a window to revise titles, c=
onsolidate duplicate entries, or reassign hours so your time appears the way =
it should on the invoice the client receives.

What you can do today:
  1. Open the attached training document and read the personalized advice.
  2. Skim the CSV to see your specific flagged entries.
  3. Going forward, follow the six general rules at the bottom of the trainin=
g doc =E2=80=94 most flags disappear when titles are descriptive and same-tic=
ket entries are consolidated.

If anything in the analysis looks wrong (mis-classified work, a one-off P1 in=
cident that genuinely needed the time), reply with the date and ticket and I =
will adjust the rules so it does not flag next time.

Thanks,
Ravi

